\item In the scoring function, we use a for loop to search for the positive or negtive word in one specific string. It is fairly easy to achieve by lookup each word in the word list and record number of positive words and negtive words and calculate the difference bweteen them. However, we also have to get rid of the repetitive count when two positive words or two negative words contain one of the other. The for loop firstly run through negative words and delete repetitive terms and executes in the same way for positive words. 

