\section*{Results}

The result shows that the p-value is $9.03*10^{-11}$ and the $R^2$ is around 0.27. When we run the granger test oppositely to test whether price is the predictive factor of emotional level, p-value is 0.6, which fails to reject the null hypothesis. The other interesting observation is that the most emotional levels distribute in the range that is lower than 0. 


